A parliamentary committee has reprimanded Embakasi East MP Babu Owino and his Starehe counterpart Charles Njagua after they were involved in a scuffle. The Powers and Privileges Committee, chaired by National Assembly Speaker Justin Muturi, said the MPs' behaviour had invited Parliament to ridicule and lowered its dignity. ALSO READ:

Hockey: Limping Jaguars face top league extinction Muturi directed the duo to apologise, on the floor of the House, for conducting themselves in a manner that reflected negatively on the dignity and integrity of the National Assembly and its members. In its report yesterday, the committee also established that the MPs' actions were a breach of privilege and punishable by law. Mr Owino and Mr Njagua fought in full glare of media at the Parliament Media Centre on October 10, last year.